            <td class="num score-cell">88.84</td>
            <td>Official Redis Labs, all data structures</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>MongoDB / Atlas</td>
            <td><a href="/tool/mongodb-js--mongodb-mcp-server/" class="tool-link">mongodb-mcp-server</a></td>
            <td class="num score-cell">88.56</td>
            <td>Official, 84% close rate, Atlas support</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Tableau / BI</td>
            <td><a href="/tool/tableau--tableau-mcp/" class="tool-link">tableau-mcp</a></td>
            <td class="num score-cell">84.32</td>
            <td>Official Tableau, workbook + data access</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>MySQL</td>
            <td><a href="/tool/benborla--mcp-server-mysql/" class="tool-link">mcp-server-mysql</a></td>
            <td class="num score-cell">85.22</td>
            <td>Read-only, 1,361 stars, safe for production</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Airflow (Astronomer)</td>
            <td><a href="/tool/astronomer--agents/" class="tool-link">astronomer/agents</a></td>
            <td class="num score-cell">77.89</td>
            <td>AI agent tooling for managed Airflow</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>dbt Core / Cloud</td>
            <td><a href="/tool/dbt-labs--dbt-mcp/" class="tool-link">dbt-mcp</a></td>
            <td class="num score-cell">76.04</td>
            <td>Official dbt Labs, run models + tests</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Multi-DB (SQLAlchemy)</td>
            <td><a href="/tool/runekaagaard--mcp-alchemy/" class="tool-link">mcp-alchemy</a></td>
            <td class="num score-cell">74.93</td>
            <td>100% issue close, widest DB coverage</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Google BigQuery</td>
            <td><a href="/tool/LucasHild--mcp-server-bigquery/" class="tool-link">mcp-server-bigquery</a></td>
            <td class="num score-cell">75.28</td>
            <td>Only mature BigQuery MCP in the index</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Apache Airflow (self-managed)</td>
            <td><a href="/tool/yangkyeongmo--mcp-server-apache-airflow/" class="tool-link">mcp-server-apache-airflow</a></td>
            <td class="num score-cell">71.10</td>
            <td>Airflow REST API, DAG management</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section id="methodology">
      <h2>Scoring methodology</h2>
      <p class="methodology">
        AgentRank scores combine five GitHub signals: stars (15%), commit freshness (25%), issue close rate (25%),
        contributor count (10%), and inbound dependents (25%). Scores are updated nightly from live crawl data.
        The average score across all {stats.totalDataTools} data-category tools is {stats.avgDataScore}.
        <a href="/methodology/" class="inline-link">Full methodology &rarr;</a>
      </p>

      <div class="cta-box">
        <p>
          <strong>See all {stats.totalDataTools} data engineering tools ranked.</strong> The full leaderboard
          updates nightly with fresh crawl data — scores shift as maintainers commit, close issues, and gain stars.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="/category/data-science/" class="inline-link">Browse all data MCP servers &rarr;</a>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;
          <a href="/" class="inline-link">Full leaderboard &rarr;</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="post-footer">
      <p class="methodology">
        Data sourced from the AgentRank nightly crawl of 25,000+ GitHub repositories.
        Scores reflect the March 19, 2026 snapshot.
        <a href="/methodology/">Scoring methodology</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="share-line">
        Found this useful? <a href="https://agentrank-ai.com/blog/best-mcp-servers-data-pipelines-etl/" class="inline-link">Share this post</a>
        or explore the <a href="/" class="inline-link">full AgentRank leaderboard</a>.
      </p>
    </footer>

    <BlogSubscribeCTA />
    <RelatedPosts posts={relatedPosts} />
    <RelatedCategories currentCategory="data-science" />
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .blog-post {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem 4rem;
  }

  .post-header {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .post-header h1 {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .post-meta {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .post-meta .sep {
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .lede {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text);
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .toc {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
  }

  .toc strong {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .toc ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
  }

  .toc a {
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

